    <xs:attribute name="shape" use="optional">
      <xs:annotation>
        <xs:documentation xml:lang="en">The shape attribute should be only used for spatial
          segments. It can be used to define either polygons, circles or cubic BÃ©zir curves. In the
          first case use a set of coordinate pairs x,y (in 2-dimensional contexts) or triples x,y,z
          (in 3-dimensional contexts) as value for the coords attribute. In the second case use a
          single triple x,y,r as value for the coords attribute (refer to the documentation of the
          coords attribute). In the third case, use at least a set of four coordinate
          pairs.</xs:documentation>
